<!-- 1.1.16 -->
<div class="toload definition">
<p><span class="envidentifier">Definition 1.1.16</span>
If $\mathcal{G}$ is a groupoid and $x\in\mathcal{G}^{(0)}$, we call the set $\mathcal{G}_x^x$ the <em>isotropy group</em> of $\mathcal{G}$ at $x$.
</p>
</div>